    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - TRANSFER CASES - ASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc id="x1303402" svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="10">
            <title>LOWER SHAFT</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303439">Figure 39.</hotlnk>
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303439" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303439.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 39. Lower Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place lower output gear into housing HUB UP and slide into position
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303440">(Figure 40)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1303440" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303440.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 40. Place Lower Output Gear Into Housing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a driver and soft hammer to install bearing into small bore of housing
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303441">(Figure 41)</hotlnk>. Recess approximately 6.35 mm (.250 inch).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1303441" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303441.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 41. Install Bearing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position gasket onto housing, aligning bolt holes and oil groove
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303442">(Figure 42)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1303442" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303442.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 42. Position Gasket Onto Housing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If shaft that requires snap ring is used, disregard Steps 4 and 5 until after shaft is
                        installed.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Put a light coat of lubricant on seal and install into bearing cap.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place bearing cap onto housing. Make sure oil groove in bearing cap is aligned with oil
                    groove in housing
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303443">(Figure 43)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1303443" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303443.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 43. Align Oil Grooves</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure with six (6) bolts and lockwashers. Tighten bolts to 43 to 50 Nm (32 to 37
                    ft-lbs),
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303444">(Figure 44)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1303444" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303444.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 44. Secure Bearing Cap Onto Housing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn assembly over.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press bearing onto shaft. Install spacer onto shaft
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303445">(Figure 45).</hotlnk>
                </para>
                <figure id="f1303445" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303445.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 45. Press Bearing Onto Shaft</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Holding the spacer and bearing, turn shaft over and install in gear
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303446">(Figure 46).</hotlnk>
                </para>
                <figure id="f1303446" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303446.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 46. Install Shaft Into Gear</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a driver and soft hammer to install shaft
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303447">(Figure 47)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1303447" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303447.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 47. Install Shaft</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install end yoke or companion flange
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1303448">(Figure 48)</hotlnk>. Secure with washer and new self-locking nut. Tighten
                    nut to 542 to 610 Nm (400 to 450 ft-lbs).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1303448" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303448.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 48. Install End Yoke or Companion Flange</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
